Access CLI commands relating to interfaces

Usage:
  drpcli interfaces [command]

Available Commands:
  exists      See if a interfaces exists by id
  indexes     Get indexes for interfaces
  list        List all interfaces
  show        Show a single interfaces by id
  wait        Wait for a interface's field to become a value within a number of seconds

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for interfaces

Global Flags:
  -d, --debug               Whether the CLI should run in debug mode
  -E, --endpoint string     The Digital Rebar Provision API endpoint to talk to (default "https://127.0.0.1:8092")
  -f, --force               When needed, attempt to force the operation - used on some update/patch calls
  -F, --format string       The serialzation we expect for output.  Can be "json" or "yaml" (default "json")
  -P, --password string     password of the Digital Rebar Provision user (default "r0cketsk8ts")
  -r, --ref string          A reference object for update commands that can be a file name, yaml, or json blob
  -T, --token string        token of the Digital Rebar Provision access
  -t, --trace string        The log level API requests should be logged at on the server side
  -Z, --traceToken string   A token that individual traced requests should report in the server logs
  -U, --username string     Name of the Digital Rebar Provision user to talk to (default "rocketskates")

Use "drpcli interfaces [command] --help" for more information about a command.
